import Docs from "../../layouts/Docs.astro";
---
<Docs title="Commands" description="Reference for slash commands available in omegon sessions.">
  <h1>Command Reference</h1>

  <h2>Session Control</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>/effort [tier]</code></td><td>View or change effort tier (Servitor → Omnissiah). Controls model, thinking, extraction, compaction, and cleave settings.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/context [pin &lt;class&gt;]</code></td><td>Inspect context class routing state. Pin a minimum context floor.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/providers</code></td><td>Show provider auth status and per-tier routing summary.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/dashboard</code></td><td>Toggle the live TUI dashboard overlay.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/compact</code></td><td>Trigger context compaction to free context window space.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Development Lifecycle</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>/cleave</code></td><td>Decompose and parallelize the current task via git worktrees.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/assess [cleave|diff|spec|design]</code></td><td>Run adversarial review, diff review, spec verification, or design readiness check.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/init</code></td><td>Initialize project memory and project orientation.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>OpenSpec</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>/opsx:propose</code></td><td>Create a new OpenSpec change proposal.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/opsx:spec</code></td><td>Generate or add specs to a change.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/opsx:ff</code></td><td>Fast-forward: generate design.md and tasks.md from specs.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/opsx:status</code></td><td>Show all active OpenSpec changes.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/opsx:verify</code></td><td>Verify specs are satisfied by implementation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/opsx:archive</code></td><td>Archive a completed change to baseline.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>System</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>/bootstrap</code></td><td>First-time setup — provider auth, capabilities, onboarding.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/update</code></td><td>Update omegon to the latest version.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/status</code></td><td>Project status overview — open designs, active changes, recent facts.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Agent Tools</h2>
  <p>In addition to slash commands, the agent has access to structured tools that it calls autonomously:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>set_model_tier</code> / <code>set_thinking_level</code> — adjust inference parameters</li>
    <li><code>memory_store</code> / <code>memory_recall</code> / <code>memory_query</code> — manage project memory</li>
    <li><code>design_tree</code> / <code>design_tree_update</code> — query and mutate the design tree</li>
    <li><code>cleave_assess</code> / <code>cleave_run</code> — assess complexity and execute decomposition</li>
    <li><code>openspec_manage</code> — manage OpenSpec lifecycle</li>
    <li><code>read</code> / <code>edit</code> / <code>write</code> / <code>bash</code> / <code>view</code> — file and system operations</li>
  </ul>
</Docs>
